Parliament, Tuesday, 26 February 2019 – The Portfolio Committee on Justice and Correctional Services will tomorrow, 27 February 2019, receive a briefing from the Ministry of Justice and Correctional Services on the status of Bosasa contracts and the implications of these for the Ministry/Department of Correctional Services. Details are as follows: 
	
	Date: Wednesday, 27 February 2019
	Time: 09:00 am
	Venue: Committee Room V454, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building. ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON JUSTICE AND CORRECTIONAL SERVICES, MS MADIPOANE MOTHAPO. For media enquiries or interviews, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Rajaa Azzakani (Ms)
	Tel: 021 403 8437
	Cell: 081 703 9542
	E-mail: razzakani@parliament.gov.za Committees have the power to summons any person to appear before them to give evidence or produce documents. They may ask any person or institution to report to them and may receive petitions, representations or submissions from the public. They play a crucial role in the law-making process.Read more